%% Platform Data Flow Diagram - Red Hat OpenShift AI 3.4-ea.1
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant Browser as Web Browser
    participant Gateway as data-science-gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant AuthProxy as kube-auth-proxy<br/>EnvoyFilter ext_authz
    participant Dashboard as ODH Dashboard<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant NotebookCtrl as Notebook Controller
    participant Notebook as Notebook Pod<br/>(User Namespace)
    participant KServe as KServe Controller<br/>(kserve namespace)
    participant ModelCtrl as odh-model-controller
    participant DSPO as DSPO API Server<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Argo as Argo Workflow Controller
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant ModelReg as Model Registry<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant PostgreSQL as PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP

    Note over User,PostgreSQL: Workflow 1: Model Development to Deployment

    User->>Browser: Access RHOAI Dashboard
    Browser->>Gateway: GET https://rh-ai.{domain}/<br/>TLS 1.3
    Gateway->>AuthProxy: ext_authz check<br/>OAuth2/OIDC
    AuthProxy-->>Gateway: Auth OK (Bearer Token)
    Gateway->>Dashboard: Forward request<br/>kube-rbac-proxy SubjectAccessReview
    Dashboard-->>Browser: Dashboard UI

    User->>Dashboard: Create Notebook Workbench
    Dashboard->>NotebookCtrl: Create Notebook CR
    NotebookCtrl->>Notebook: Create StatefulSet + HTTPRoute<br/>+ kube-rbac-proxy sidecar<br/>+ NetworkPolicy

    User->>Notebook: Develop & Train Model
    Notebook->>S3: Upload trained model<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+

    User->>Dashboard: Create InferenceService
    Dashboard->>KServe: Create InferenceService CR
    KServe->>S3: Download model artifacts<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+
    KServe->>KServe: Create serving pods<br/>+ HTTPRoute/VirtualService
    ModelCtrl->>KServe: Watch InferenceService
    ModelCtrl->>ModelCtrl: Create Route + NetworkPolicy<br/>+ ServiceMonitor
    ModelCtrl->>ModelReg: Sync metadata<br/>HTTPS/443
    ModelReg->>PostgreSQL: Store model metadata<br/>TCP/5432

    Note over User,PostgreSQL: Workflow 2: Pipeline-Orchestrated Training

    User->>Dashboard: Create DSPA in project
    Dashboard->>DSPO: Create DSPA CR
    DSPO->>DSPO: Deploy API Server + Argo<br/>+ MLMD + MariaDB + S3

    User->>DSPO: Submit pipeline<br/>HTTPS/8443 kube-rbac-proxy
    DSPO->>Argo: Create Workflow CR
    Argo->>Argo: Orchestrate pipeline steps
    Argo->>S3: Store pipeline artifacts<br/>HTTPS/443
    Argo->>KServe: Create InferenceService CR
    KServe->>S3: Download model
    Argo->>ModelReg: Register model version<br/>HTTPS/443

    Note over User,PostgreSQL: Workflow 3: Distributed Training with Ray

    participant KubeRay as KubeRay Operator
    participant RayHead as Ray Head Node
    participant RayWorker as Ray Workers

    User->>KubeRay: Create RayCluster CR
    KubeRay->>RayHead: Create head pod + services
    KubeRay->>RayWorker: Create worker pods
    KubeRay->>KubeRay: Create HTTPRoute + NetworkPolicy<br/>+ cert-manager mTLS certs
    User->>Gateway: Access Ray Dashboard<br/>HTTPS/443
    Gateway->>AuthProxy: ext_authz check
    AuthProxy-->>Gateway: Auth OK
    Gateway->>RayHead: Forward to Ray Dashboard<br/>kube-rbac-proxy/8265
    User->>RayHead: Submit training job
    RayHead->>RayWorker: Distribute work<br/>mTLS (cert-manager)

    Note over User,PostgreSQL: Workflow 4: LLM Evaluation & Guardrails

    participant TrustyAI as TrustyAI Operator
    participant LMEval as LMEval Pod
    participant Guardrails as Guardrails Orchestrator

    User->>TrustyAI: Create LMEvalJob CR
    TrustyAI->>LMEval: Create eval pod<br/>+ Kueue workload scheduling
    LMEval->>KServe: Run benchmarks against LLM<br/>HTTP/HTTPS
    LMEval->>S3: Store eval results<br/>HTTPS/443

    User->>TrustyAI: Create GuardrailsOrchestrator CR
    TrustyAI->>Guardrails: Deploy orchestrator<br/>+ auto-discover InferenceServices
    Browser->>Guardrails: Inference request
    Guardrails->>Guardrails: Run detectors
    Guardrails->>KServe: Forward to LLM<br/>if safe
    KServe-->>Guardrails: LLM response
    Guardrails-->>Browser: Guarded response
